		<div id="comment_body_64146599"><p>I would even accept better nickel-and-diming.  Want to have your hot new show exclusive to your platform?  Fine.  Let me pay $0.99 to watch an episode to see if I like it.  That's cheaper than a free trial for people who will forget to cancel.</p><p>And why is Roku the only one implementing a Universal Search algorithm?  Can't the platforms get together and do this outside of a single vendor's device?  I just want to go to the web and type in the name of a movie or show and see what platform it is even on - because nobody remembers.</p></div>
